 Q1.Difference between Block storage & Object Storage ?
Ans:-Block storage and object storage are both types of data storage commonly used in the realm of computing, but they differ in their architecture, use cases, and how they handle data.
     Block storage is akin to traditional storage systems with structured data, suitable for applications that need direct and fast access to raw storage blocks.

     Object storage is designed for scalable and distributed data, with each piece of data treated as an independent object. It is well-suited for large-scale, distributed, and globally accessible storage needs.

Q2. Difference between static website & dynamic website ?
Ans:-Static websites are simpler, faster, and easier to host but are limited in terms of interactivity and real-time updates.
     Dynamic websites offer a more interactive and personalized user experience but require server-side processing and are typically more complex to develop and maintain.

Q3.What are the naming rules ?
Ans:-Good: my-awesome-s3-bucket
     Avoid: My Awesome S3 Bucket

Q4.What is the major resource of S3 Bucket ?
Ans:-In Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service), the major resource is the bucket. A bucket is a container for objects (files) stored in Amazon S3. 
     It's a top-level entity within S3, and each object is contained within a bucket. Buckets provide a way to organize and control access to your data in Amazon S3.

