Q6.What is versioning & Why do we need versioning ?
Ans:-versioning provides a structured way to manage changes, collaborate effectively, and maintain a reliable history of your work. 
    It's a fundamental concept in software development, document management, and collaborative projects.

Q7.What are the objects and types of objects that we are uploading into the S3 Bucket ?
Ans:-
     In Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service), an "object" is the fundamental entity stored in the service. 
     Objects are typically files such as documents, images, videos, or any other type of binary or text data. 
     Each object consists of data, a key (unique within a bucket), and metadata. Here are some common types of objects that are frequently uploaded into S3 buckets.

Q8.Why is MFA Delete important in S3 Bucket object level ?
Ans:-MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication) Delete is an additional layer of security provided by Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service) to help protect sensitive data stored in S3 buckets, especially at the object level. 
     When MFA Delete is enabled for a versioned S3 bucket, it requires the use of MFA authentication before allowing the deletion of versions of objects.

Q9.What is S3 Multipart upload ?
Ans:-Amazon S3 Multipart Upload is a feature of Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3) that allows you to upload large objects in parts. 
     This feature is particularly useful when dealing with very large files, such as videos or large datasets, where uploading the entire file in a single request might not be efficient or practical. 
     Multipart Upload provides advantages in terms of performance, resumability, and efficiency.

Q10.What are the storage classes in Amazon S3 ?  
Ans:-Amazon S3 offers several storage classes, each designed to meet different needs in terms of data access, durability, and cost.
     The choice of storage class depends on factors such as how frequently you access your data, the speed at which you need to retrieve it, and cost considerations.

